ref="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stable" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stable" target="_blank">stable</a> but jobs are downIn 2009 there was 410400 total jobs in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a> by 2010 it had fallen to 387700 and the latest <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Statistics" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Statistics" target="_blank">stats</a> for 2013 show it at 386500The big drop has been in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Full-time" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Full-time" target="_blank">full time</a> jobs with the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Part-time" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Part-time" target="_blank">part time</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Workforce" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Workforce" target="_blank">workforce</a> increasingFull <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_%28magazine%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_%28magazine%29" target="_blank">time</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laborer" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laborer" target="_blank">workers</a> dropped from 286800 in 2009 to 258800 in 2013 while <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Part-time" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Part-time" target="_blank">part time</a> staff increased from114000 in 2010 to 127000 in 2013Wages of those resident in the city increased modestly over the last parliamentGross Weekly <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Payment" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Payment" target="_blank">pay</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Median" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Median" target="_blank">Median</a> in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a> residents <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose" target="_blank">rose</a> from &pound452 in 2010 to &pound497 in 2014 <a h